# Collector Patterns

## Thread safety

Collectors run in daemon threads. Push results to UI via `queue_fn`:

```python
def _loop(self) -> None:
    while not self._stop.is_set():
        data = self._collect()
        self.queue_fn(lambda d=data: self.on_data(d))
        self._stop.wait(self.interval_s)
```

## Return plain dicts

Every collector function returns `Dict[str, Any]`. No custom classes or dataclasses for data transfer.

## Subprocess rules

- Always set `timeout=` (8s for DNS, 120s for speed/traceroute)
- Always use `capture_output=True, text=True`
- Catch `subprocess.TimeoutExpired` and `FileNotFoundError` separately
- Check tool availability with `shutil.which()` before first use

## CoreWLAN specifics

- Wrap every attribute access in try/except — PyObjC can throw on any call
- SSID/BSSID may be None without Location Services — not an error
- Use `scanForNetworksWithName_error_(None, None)` — returns (result, error) tuple
- PHY mode constants vary between macOS versions (int vs bitflags) — map both
